FBIS4-56786 "drlat090_a_94005" FBIS-LAT-94-090 Daily Report 10 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Message to Mandela Advocates Ties Message to Mandela Advocates Ties FL1005015694 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 0000 GMT 10 May 94 FL1005015694 Havana Cuba Vision Network Spanish BFN [Text] On 9 May, it was made known that Fidel Castro wrote a message to Mandela. The text of the message highlights the happiness of the Cuban people with the creation of a democratic, multiracial government headed by an antiapartheid leader. Castro expressed Cuba's willingness to establish diplomatic relations, as well as to assist and support the Government of South Africa during this new phase.
